metadata.name: Separation in the Night #227
metadata.description:
For this project I was strongly inspired by the paintings of Mark Rothko, Jackson Pollock, Kazemir Malevich, but mostly token refers to the works of one of the largest figures of the European avant-garde, Paul Klee. I wanted to convey that complex color mood and atmosphere that artist achieved with oil paints. 
I have been working with color palettes and functions for a long time to make complex transitions and gradients. This code has really huge potential for a wide diversity of artworks and I would like to see as many interesting variations as possible. Enjoy<3

Project contains:

•three canvas types : horizontal, vertical, square
•rare features : vertical stripes, posterization
•press "p" to pause animation and play again
•open in tab and press "s" to save .png


Made in P5.js by @Georginerous

metadata.name: the Black Blocks #35
metadata.description: Beauty in asymmetry and random events, combining black boxes, creates an abstract and unexpected atmosphere. The space between black and white invites the eyes to a graphic party full of modern and intimate abstract concepts.

metadata.name: ZOOM (4hwf) #84
metadata.description:
"Das System lässt keine Überraschung zu. Überraschung ist Ausdruck partieller Unkenntnis. Überraschung weist auf Mangel von Wissen hin, deutet Leerstellen an. Bisher hatten sie keine Leerstellen festgestellt." — Herbert W. Franke

ZOOM explores linear scaling of pixels by zooming into a noisy framebuffer. Various zoom levels are composed one below the other, becoming a cinematic animation through iteration of the hue values of the pixels in the framebuffer.

In Gedenken an Herbert W. Franke
Kim Asendorf, 2022

metadata.name: Ailerons #59
metadata.description:
Ailerons, littering the factory floor, custom made and ready to be fitted to their respective aircraft. An accent trickles across the canvas, coloring any object in its path.

A study of light, built entirely in a 2d renderer, creating light and shadow with math and logic.

Press 's' to save a .png

Created with p5.js and chroma.js

metadata.name: GEN XYZ Das Occult #673
metadata.description:
A 10k Generative Profile Pic collection
GEN XYZ Das Occult - by culla - @tamccullough

move over cryptopunks
there is a new group on the scene

100% code - not an image composition

A bunch of common palettes
A selection of rare palettes
And a smaller set of ultra rare palettes
However, rarity will be based on what combinations the code produces

The majority of tokens will not have a special trait
However your token might have one or even multiple special traits
But, be aware that only the last special trait added will be listed in the features

Even then, look closely, because not all aspects of the canvas are included in the features. Collectors should still look closely and choose what they like when buying on secondary.

Which team are you on? X or O?

follow culla on twitter for updates. Or maybe __acolyte__

If the non reserved tokens mint out quickly, Access List mints will have 24 hours to mint reserves assigned to those wallets

Thank you for supporting an emerging artist in the generative art space

Access List reserves were given to holders of the following PFP collections created by culla
2x for each Basqunk held
1x for each Inkspunk, TwoFourQunk, V0iD, DeeManz, Punkasso and CR0$$KULL
You would have needed to transfer the above tokens to your mint wallet at the time of the snapshot

share your tokens on social media with #genxyznft
Made with love by culla using p5.js

metadata.name: Noisy Gardens #207
metadata.description:
I had a wonderful childhood. I grew up near a big lake, in a house with a huge garden. You could get lost for the whole day, building houses on trees, collecting flowers and stones or stealing food from the vegetable garden. Having a brother of the same age made things even better, endless adventures with somebody saving you every time you are too dumb to realize you are walking into troubles.

We enjoyed the summers with the hot days, the fireflies and the nights full of falling stars. The winters with the snow, the stalactites and our box turtle disappearing for months to then reappear in the spring (Until she did not).

At the same time, taking care of the garden was a big responsibility, affecting our family life in many ways. Numerous times, I felt like the efforts we were putting in to keep it in order were never enough and nature was always faster in restoring her point of view. A struggle that affects us humans since we started to bend nature at our will, thousands of years ago.

In my gardens, I tried to capture this struggle, this constant fight to shape nature at our will.
However, I also tried to represent the beauty that can be found in both savage and human shaped nature, if shaped with love and respect.

I dedicate this project to my grandfather, who gave us a garden.
I am sure he would have loved it.

---

Hand coded with love and obsession. 💚

Powered by p5, p5.createLoop and chroma.

======> COMMANDS (In Live Mode) <======

Press ‘s’ to save the current output.
Press ‘m’ to open a menu with the available outputs.

The generation of a hi-res image, up to 8000x8000, takes a few seconds.
The generation of an Animated GIF takes several minutes and the save command works only once the GIF is complete.

Settings are passed as URL parameters that can be used to load different configurations.

- mode = 0 | 1
0 For static PNG images, 1 for animated GIFs

- size = s | m | l
The Size of the output, 1080x1080, 4000x4000, 8000x8000 for static images and 512x512, 800x800, 1080x1080 for animated GIFs

- fps = 10 | 15 | 20 | 25 | 30
Frames per second of animated GIFs
